Police say a preliminary investigation suggests that the wild cats were poisoned. JOHANNESBURG Three lions have been killed for their paws and heads at a farm outside Polokwane.Officials say they are concerned about the rising killing of the animals in the province, with a total of 9 lions being found dead in the last few months in Tzaneen, Hoedspruit and Mara areas.Police say a preliminary investigation suggests that the wild cats were poisoned.The police's Motlafela Mojapelo said, Three more lions were found dead with poison and we are investigating unlawful hunting. 